29.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Hmm, Nerfed?</span><hr size=1> The day before yesterday I was able to do missions solo at 50%-60% difficulty.  Greens were alot easier to kill, and yellows, which are supposed to be even in level, were difficult to kill but not impossible, about 50/50 chance depending on if I used my first aid.<br>
<br>
Yesterday I noticed a massive change.  Greens are now as difficult as yellows, and yellows are now like oranges and I can't even put a dent in them, I died 5 times trying.  None of this makes any logical sense. Either I was nerfed or the mobs were majorly buffed up beyond reason.  Anyone else notice this sudden change?  If they keep pulling these Verant maneuvers I'll move along elsewhere. <p><center><a href="http://www.silentsentinels.com"><img src="http://www.vanitey.com/signature.jpg" border=0 align=bottom></a></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#F5F5DC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/udreadstar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>dreadstar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Dervish Cutthroat</span><br>  Posts: 199<br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/25/01 7:34:51 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fluclin71335frm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=129.topic&index=1>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Hmm, Nerfed?</span><hr size=1> I kind of posted this in that other thread, but I was thinking the same thing.  That I should be able to kill greens easy especially after leveling.  But I have to remind myself 2 things..<br>
<br>
1)  Missions are generated for your level.  So even though they have the same name, and might be green.  They are also tougher.<br>
2)  QL of weapon I think is really what makes a big difference.  Every few levels you really need to get a higher level weapon to keep above the curve.  Once you fall behind, things will become tougher..<br>
<br>
Once I upgraded my weapon, I can now take high greens with no problem, where the weapon I had before (same level though) I could hardly put a dent in them unless they were really low greens.<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/urasisanthecursed.showPublicProfile?language=EN>RasisanThecursed</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Will O Wisp</span><br>  Posts: 150<br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/25/01 7:40:05 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fluclin71335frm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=129.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.fortunecity.com/rivendell/lair/880/animation/greydragonsnim.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Hmm, Nerfed?</span><hr size=1> I have been use the same diffcultly lvl since I started and yesterday when I did this all the mobs where grey (no exp) and they where just as hard. When I turned the misson lvl diff. up It was almost impossiable but fun. When your a tank beatn down 3 mobs at a time makes you feel goood ( all greens might I add). <p>Rasisan of Fearless Crusaders & Nesader, Vassal of Thor's Hammer, Follower of Sir Sorlak</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#F5F5DC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uhuffwinwindbane.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Huffwin Windbane</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Orc Legionairre</span><br>  Posts: 92<br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/25/01 7:47:27 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fluclin71335frm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=129.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Hmm, Nerfed?</span><hr size=1> I had little problem yesturday, I do all mine at 50% but I make sure I have the order bar all the way over so that way generally I only have to fight one at a time, but sometimes they add if i am not careful.<br>
Greens were getting very difficult for me for a while, then I realized I am lvl 17 using q11 weapons, once I upgraded to lvl 17 axes I tore them up like I am supposed to, I used to be able to take oranges, but now I am having a rough time with some yellows, mainly the tank classes.<br>
I think upgrading your weapons is huge though.<br>
I also have to add that missions are hit or miss, some missions I have all greys and a few greens and only get like 2k xp total, other missions on the same difficulty I get all yellows, takes almost an hour, but I get over half a lvl in xp, so it really is very random.  You could have just run into a tough stretch of missions.<br>
For me the difficulty of the mission is in what classes I am fighting, if I am fighting a lot of enforcers I have to rest very often and can only take one a time, 2 if I have dimach up (it now takes off half a life bar in one hit) if it is a mission with a lot of nano techs then I fly through it since they have almost no hp and they dont run away after eye gouging, so I can hit them blind.<br>
Oh and I finally got my first full suit of Nomad armor, shame that once I completed it it is almost outdated on me, oh well, at least I look cool<br>
Paelian<br>
