Those and enforcers are really the only yellows that give me a hard time, a yellow engineer or nanotech fold like a cheap table, sometimes I don't have to heal afterward, but I always have to use med packs after traders and enforcers.  Its just the mob, green enforcers are pretty easy since their ac isn't as high so my axe hits near full dmg every time.  I just hope this doesn't get like eq where an even con at high lvls means you are toast even if you are up on your equipment.<br>
<br>
Paelian <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ulieah.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lieah</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://wwp.icq.com/scripts/online.dll?icq=70896971&img=5 BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sarnak Knight</span><br>  Posts: 825<br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/25/01 10:17:18 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fluclin71335frm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=129.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Hmm, Nerfed?</span><hr size=1> Ok so I need to go Rifle hunting again, and to think I just got this one.  Thanks.  My armor could probably use help, I'll probably just do easy easy missions and get bunches of money to buy it all. <p><center><a href="http://www.silentsentinels.com"><img src="http://www.vanitey.com/signature.jpg" border=0 align=bottom></a></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#F5F5DC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ulieah.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lieah</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://wwp.icq.com/scripts/online.dll?icq=70896971&img=5 BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sarnak Knight</span><br>  Posts: 826<br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/26/01 4:40:20 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fluclin71335frm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=129.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Hmm, Nerfed?</span><hr size=1> Yep nevermind I was being quick to condemn.  Managed to find a slightly better rifle.  If anyone comes across a QL 17 or 18 Ill treated blackend bastar rifle or whatever its called, it seems to have worked the best.  Also I noticed that even rifles that are different, with the same or better stats are not always better, I don't get it and I can't quite figure out why or how.<br>
